org.datalorax.populace.core.util

Class ImmutableTypeMap<V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.datalorax.populace.core.util.ImmutableTypeMap<V>

  • public class ImmutableTypeMap<V>
extends java.lang.Object
    Immutable collection of handlers for specific and more generic types. Values can be registered against a Type key as one of:
    • Specific - meaning they match the exact registered type. This includes specific array types and parameterised types. Use ImmutableTypeMap.Builder.withSpecificType(java.lang.reflect.Type, T) to register.
    • Super - meaning they match any sub-type of the registered raw class Use ImmutableTypeMap.Builder.withSuperType(java.lang.Class<?>, T) to register.
    • Default - meaning they will be returned if no other key matches the requested type and the requested type is not an array type. Use ImmutableTypeMap.Builder.withDefault(T) to register.
    • Default Array - meaning they will be used if no other key matches the requested type and the requested type is an array type. * Use ImmutableTypeMap.Builder.withArrayDefault(T) to register.

    Values can be retrieved via get(java.lang.reflect.Type)}
